text.Taxonomy and naming:
The species was first formally described by Ferdinand von Mueller in 1861 and the description was published in Fragmenta Phytographiae Australiae. The specific epithet (bowmanii) honours the collector of the type specimen, Edward M. Bowman, a station worker.Three subspecies have been identified:

E. bowmanii F.Muell. subsp. bowmanii which has linear leaves with their edges rolled under;
E. bowmanii subsp. latifolia (L.S.Sm.) Chinnock  which has leaves that are flat, lance- or egg-shaped with the narrower end towards the base, and spreading flowers;
E. bowmanii subsp. nutans Chinnock which has egg-shaped to almost circular leaves with thickened edges, and flowers that hang from their stalks.
